While the number of divorce cases is almost the same regardless of the education level and income of the women, there was an increase recorded in divorce cases involving women with high economic status. The percentage of women who are divorced is higher compared to women who are widowed and is higher among the more affluent ethnic Albanians then the other ethnic groups of Kosovo. Property division receives more attention during negotiations between the husband and wife Lawyers interviewed added that women with economic self-sufficiency and powerful social and political connections are more successful when seeking greater rights after the legal procedures in terms of property division. Others indicated that women need to be more active during the whole process of seeking their legal rights and be aware and knowledgeable enough to articulate their rights during the divorce settlement.
Multiple Imputation for Non-Response Bias Analysis
IMPUTATION PROCEDURES LEAD TO BIASED ESTIMATES UNDER THE SALE 7 MEASUREMENT FRAMEWORK. Imputation procedures are generally used when a sample doesn’t have information on a question that is used in an analysis. For example, children under schooling age in a household are used in the calculation of the Useage Index (MICS3). Taking into account children who are not in school as children of attendance would lead to false estimates. Multiple imputation methods are used most often to replace missing values through a series of conditional imputations that mimic the process of data generation.
